Complete Git workflow after setup
git status => on which branch ,Changes to be committed, Changes not staged for commit, Untracked files
git add => git add is used to move changes from your working directory to the staging area.
git add Documentation src pom.xml Readme.md => Adds only the mentioned files/folders to staging
git add . => This is a bulk add command . Adds ALL changes in current directory:New/Modified/Deleted files
git commit =>git commit saves your staged changes permanently into the Git repository.
git commit -m "added login testcase" => -m stands for message
👉 It allows you to write a commit message directly in the command line
git push =>git push is used to upload your committed changes from your local repository to a remote repository (like GitHub).
git push origin QA  =>Push my local main branch to the remote repository named origin . Used When branch is already linked to remote
git push → Upload changes , origin → Remote repository name , QA → Branch name
git push -u origin QA  => Push the branch AND set it as upstream (default tracking branch)
-u = set-upstream
✔ First time pushing a branvh : git push -u origin QA
✔ After that: git push
👉 git push -u origin main = Push + set default branch
👉 git push origin main = Just push

